'''Peter Sauder''' is a Canadian screenwriter who is known for his Star Wars contributions to [[Star Wars: Droids: The Adventures of R2-D2 and C-3PO|''Star Wars Droids'']] ([[Nelvana]]) the animated television series (1985-1986).

===Non Star Wars contributions===
Sauder has also done a number of non Star Wars films and television series such as the ''Care Bears'' movies (whose three movies he wrote), ''Babar'' and ''Strawberry Shortcake''.

Sauder was also the head writer for the very first season (1983-84) of Inspector Gadget, as well as the Disney Channels live action series ''The Edison Twins''.

In the late 1990s, he was story editor for the computer-animated preschool show Rolie Polie Olie.

His latest project (as of 2006) is the CBC science-fiction children's show, Lunar Jim.

